spans.text: her Royal Bounty showed To one
the Goodness of a gracious QUEEN
clouded all the Joys before expressed
tell , they loath the tainted Grass
the scorching Ray , or rapid Storm
from her Bosom sent A deep presaging Sigh
to cast a gloomy Frown , While from his airy Height the Lark sunk down The tuneful Birds their joyous Songs denied
My drooping Heart , which felt unusual Weight ,
I , portend no Evil , while My Royal Mistress condescends to smile : If She's propitious , what can COLIN fear ?
exclude the Wind , or sunny Ray

I , my SYLVIA comes afield , This grateful Bower a safe Retreat shall yield : If rainy , here she may the Storms evade ; If fair , the Branches will project a Shade : Here SYLVIA shall , with COLIN , take her Rest ; And COLIN here , with SYLVIA , shall be blessed
every worthy Swain Not Godlike PAN
is the Day overcast with Gloom
my presaging Heart too rightly guessed : I silent stood , and spoke my Grief with Tears ; You know , my Heart was firmly linked to hers
my Heart was firmly linked to hers

that mutual Bond of Friendship last
the faithful SYLVIA is no more
Sighs I spend the lingering Day
stole ten of CUDDY's Lambs , A lurching Mongrel killed their bleating Dams :
a Flute , which DAMON lately made
straight a Throng Of Nymphs and Swains
